ElvClient

new ElvClient({
contentSpaceId,
hostname,
port,
useHTTPSoptional,
ethHostname,
ethPort,
ethUseHTTPSoptional,
noCacheoptional,
noAuthoptional
}) → ElvClient

Create a new ElvClient

Returns: New ElvClient connected to the specified content fabric and blockchain
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
contentSpaceId string

ID of the content space
hostname string

Hostname of the content fabric API
port string | number

Port of the content fabric API
useHTTPS boolean <optional>
 true

Use HTTPS when communicating with the fabric
ethHostname string

Hostname of the blockchain RPC endpoint
ethPort string | number

Port of the blockchain RPC endpoint
ethUseHTTPS boolean <optional>
 true

Use HTTPS when communicating with the blockchain
noCache boolean <optional>
 false

If enabled, blockchain transactions will not be cached
noAuth boolean <optional>
 false

If enabled, blockchain authorization will not be performed

async AccessRequest({
libraryIdoptional,
objectIdoptional,
versionHashoptional,
argsoptional,
updateoptional,
noCacheoptional
}) → object

Make an explicit call to accessRequest or updateRequest of the appropriate contract. Unless noCache is specified on this method or on the client, the resultant transaction hash of this method will be cached for all subsequent access to this contract.

Note: Access and update requests are handled automatically by ElvClient. Use this method only if you need to make an explicit call. For example, if you need to specify custom arguments to access a content object, you can call this method explicitly with those arguments. Since the result is cached (by default), all subsequent calls to that content object will be authorized with that AccessRequest transaction.

Note: If the access request has an associated charge, this charge will be determined and supplied automatically.

TODO: Content space and library access requests are currently disabled for performance reasons

Returns: Resultant AccessRequest or UpdateRequest event
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
libraryId string <optional>

ID of the library
objectId string <optional>

ID of the object
versionHash string <optional>

Version hash of the object
args Array <optional>
 [

Custom arguments to the accessRequest or updateRequest methods
update boolean <optional>
 false

If true, will call updateRequest instead of accessRequest
noCache boolean <optional>
 false

If true, the resultant transaction hash will not be cached for future use
Example
async AccessRequest({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",
  "objectId": "iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC",

    "",
    [],
    []
  ]
});

async BitcodeMethodUrl({
libraryId,
objectId,
versionHashoptional,
method,
queryParamsoptional,
noAuthoptional,
noCacheoptional
}) → Promise.<string>

Generate a URL to the specified /call endpoint of a content object to call a bitcode method. URL includes authorization token.

Alias for the FabricUrl method with the "call" parameter

Returns: URL to the specified rep endpoint with authorization token
See:
  • FabricUrl for creating arbitrary fabric URLs
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
libraryId string

ID of the library
objectId string

ID of the object
versionHash string <optional>

Hash of the object version - if not specified, latest version will be used
method string

Bitcode method to call
queryParams Object <optional>

Query params to add to the URL
noAuth boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, authorization will not be performed and the URL will not have an authorization token. This is useful for accessing public assets.
noCache boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, a new access request will be made for the authorization regardless of whether such a request exists in the client cache. This request will not be cached.
Examples
async BitcodeMethodUrl({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",
  "objectId": "iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC",
  "method": "image"
});


"http://localhost:8008/qlibs/ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks/q/iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC/call/image?authorization=eyJxc3BhY2VfaWQiOiJpc3BjNDU4dTd2eGtTMm85WHlFM0hvcUVLWnVaOWg4dyIsInFsaWJfaWQiOiJpbGliVEYxM2dUOVM5ZEQ1Z012R3ZHaXlFNjZ3dGtzIiwiYWRkciI6IjB4MjFFNzM2OTVkNTFEODI5RTJiYmI1ZDQyMGY0ODc3NjEzMkFFMkU0NCIsInR4aWQiOiIweDIzOTU0MzUxMWYxZjMyYjdjY2IyNzk3MzAzZTczMWRiMzA1ZWRiNWVlNzI0Yzk3NThiZWM3NTAxYzU2NDg1MWIifQ%3D%3D.U0lHTkFUVVJF"
async BitcodeMethodUrl({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",
  "objectId": "iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC",
  "method": "image",
  "noAuth": true
});


"http://localhost:8008/qlibs/ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks/q/iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC/call/image"

async CallContractMethod({
contractAddress,
abi,
methodName,
methodArgs,
valueoptional,
overridesoptional
}) → Promise.<Object>

Call the specified method on a deployed contract. This action will be performed by this client's signer.

NOTE: This method will only wait for the transaction to be created. If you want to wait for the transaction to be mined, use the CallContractMethodAndWait method.

Returns: Response containing information about the transaction
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
contractAddress string

Address of the contract to call the specified method on
abi Object

ABI of contract
methodName string

Method to call on the contract
methodArgs Array.<string>

List of arguments to the contract constructor

  • it is recommended to format these arguments using the FormatContractArguments method
value number | BigNumber <optional>

Amount of ether to include in the transaction
overrides Object <optional>

Change default gasPrice or gasLimit used for this action
Examples
async CallContractMethod({
  "contractAddress": "0x56028abff52b4a479d2c7b30de51af552c92cd20",

Source:
  • ElvClient.js, line 2213

async CallContractMethodAndWait({
contractAddress,
abi,
methodName,
methodArgs,
value,
overridesoptional
}) → Promise.<Object>

Call the specified method on a deployed contract and wait for the transaction to be mined. This action will be performed by this client's signer.

Returns: The event object of this transaction
See:
  • Utils.WeiToEther
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
contractAddress string

Address of the contract to call the specified method on
abi Object

ABI of contract
methodName string

Method to call on the contract
methodArgs Array.<string>

List of arguments to the contract constructor

  • it is recommended to format these arguments using the FormatContractArguments method
value number | BigNumber

Amount of ether to include in the transaction
overrides Object <optional>

Change default gasPrice or gasLimit used for this action
Examples

async ContentObjectAccessComplete({
objectId,
score
}) → Promise.<Object>

Call accessComplete on the specified content object contract using a previously cached requestID. Caching must be enabled and an access request must have been previously made on the specified object by this client instance.

Returns: Transaction log of the AccessComplete event
Parameters:
Name Type Description
objectId string

ID of the object
score number

Percentage score (0-100)
Example

  "objectId": "iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC",
  "score": 90

async ContentObjectByHash({versionHashoptional}) → Promise.<Object>

Note: This endpoint does not require authorization

async ContentObjectMetadata({
libraryId,
objectId,
versionHashoptional,
metadataSubtreeoptional,
noAuthoptional
}) → Promise.<Object>

Get the metadata of a content object

Returns: Metadata of the content object
See:
  • /qlibs/:qlibid/q/:qhit/meta
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
libraryId string

ID of the library
objectId string

ID of the object
versionHash string <optional>

Version of the object -- if not specified, latest version is used
metadataSubtree string <optional>

Subtree of the object metadata to retrieve
noAuth boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, authorization will not be performed for this call
Examples
async ContentObjectMetadata({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",
  "objectId": "iq__TF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks"
});


{
  "private": {
    "meta": "data"
  }
}

async ContentType({
nameoptional,
versionHashoptional
}) → Promise.<Object>

Look up content type record by name or by version hash

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
name string <optional>

Name of the content type to find
versionHash string <optional>

Version hash of the content type to find

NOTE: If looking up by name, only the latest version of content types will be searched. If a specific version is required, use the version hash.
Examples
async ContentType({
  "name": "Test Content Type 34ada2ad5608d932f195"
});


{
  "id": "iq__JTDeZd2nrjquEMYgSyXkCBKhbye",
  "hash": "hq__QmaN2rpQGteHJ2wAbnAuUzbb26nB2qAzjwpeEDYZS7Yw9f",
  "type": "",
  "meta": {
    "name": "Test Content Type 34ada2ad5608d932f195"
  }
}
async ContentType({
  "versionHash": "iq__JTDeZd2nrjquEMYgSyXkCBKhbye"
});

async ContentTypeOwner({
nameoptional,
versionHashoptional
}) → Promise.<string>

Returns the address of the owner of the specified content type

Returns: The account address of the owner
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
name string <optional>

Name of the content type to find
versionHash string <optional>

Version hash of the content type to find
Example
async ContentTypeOwner({
  "name": "Test Content Type 34ada2ad5608d932f195"
});

async ContentTypes({latestOnlyoptional}) → Promise.<Object>

List the content types available in this content space

Returns: A mapping of content type version hash to information about that content type version
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
latestOnly boolean <optional>
 true

If specified, only the most recent version of the content type will be included.

Because content types are specified by their immutable version hash, setting this option to false is useful for looking up information about existing content object types which may have been updated since the object was created.
Examples
async ContentTypes();

  • ElvClient.js, line 746

async ContractEvents({
contractAddress,
abi,
fromBlockoptional,
toBlockoptional,
includeTransactionoptional
}) → Array.<Array.<Object>>

Get all events on the specified contract

Returns: List of blocks, in ascending order by block number, each containing a list of the events in the block.
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
contractAddress string

The address of the contract
abi object

The ABI of the contract
fromBlock number <optional>

Limit results to events after the specified block (inclusive)
toBlock number <optional>

Limit results to events before the specified block (inclusive)
includeTransaction boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, more detailed transaction info will be included. Note: This requires one extra network call per block, so it should not be used for very large ranges
Example

async CopyContentObject({
libraryId,
originalVersionHash,
optionsoptional
}) → Promise.<Object>

Create a new content object draft from an existing content object version.

Note: The type of the new copy can be different from the original object.

Returns: Response containing the object ID and write token of the draft
See:
  • CreateContentObject
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
libraryId string

ID of the library in which to create the new object
originalVersionHash

Version hash of the object to copy
options Object <optional>

type: Version hash of the content type to associate with the object - may be different from the original object

meta: Metadata to use for the new object - This will be merged into the metadata of the original object
Example
async CopyContentObject({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",
  "originalVersionHash": "hq__Qmaj3n5anxFEQ6Q1c2DnvaXFd7TcjLM2o4NAxjpGyD5GXw",
  "options": {
    "type": "",
    "meta": {
      "copy": "metadata"
    },
    "copy_from": "hq__Qmaj3n5anxFEQ6Q1c2DnvaXFd7TcjLM2o4NAxjpGyD5GXw"
  }
});


{
  "id": "iq__3J2GdrB6gQuEv3HX8K1gXWZjtoxQ",
  "type": "",
  "write_token": "tqw_MAVipK8CtrVKjVcZnpWxLJjFWNSHetbrn"
}

async CreateContentLibrary({
name,
descriptionoptional,
imageoptional,
publicMetadataoptional,
privateMetadataoptional
}) → Promise.<string>

Create a new content library.

A new content library contract is deployed from the content space, and that contract ID is used to determine the library ID to create in the fabric.

Returns: Library ID of created library
See:
  • PUT /qlibs/:qlibid
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
name string

Library name
description string <optional>

Library description
image blob <optional>

Image associated with the library
publicMetadata Object <optional>

Public library metadata
privateMetadata Object <optional>

Private library metadata (metadata of library object)
Examples
async CreateContentLibrary({
  "name": "Test Library 34ada2ad5608d932f195",
  "description": "Test Library Description",
  "image": "<ArrayBuffer 101254>",
  "publicMetadata": {
    "public": {
      "toReplace": {
        "meta": "data"
      },
      "toDelete": {
        "meta": "data"
      }
    }
  },
  "privateMetadata": {
    "private": {
      "meta": "data"
    }
  }

async DeployContract({
abi,
bytecode,
constructorArgs,
overridesoptional
}) → Promise.<Object>

Deploy a contract from ABI and bytecode. This client's signer will be the owner of the contract.

Returns: Response containing the deployed contract address and the transaction hash of the deployment
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description

ABI of contract

constructorArgs Array.<string>

async DownloadFile({
libraryId,
objectId,
versionHashoptional,
filePath,
formatoptional
}) → Promise.<(Blob|ArrayBuffer)>

Download a file from a content object

Returns: Part data as a blob
See:
  • GET /qlibs/:qlibid/q/:qhit/files/:filePath
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
libraryId string

ID of the library
objectId string

ID of the object
versionHash string <optional>

Hash of the object version - if not specified, latest version will be used
filePath string

Path to the file to download
format string <optional>
 "blob"

Format in which to return the data ("blob" | "arraybuffer")
Examples
async DownloadFile({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",

async Events({
toBlockoptional,
fromBlockoptional,
countoptional,
includeTransactionoptional
}) → Array.<Array.<Object>>

Get events from the blockchain in reverse chronological order, starting from toBlock. This will also attempt to identify and parse any known Eluvio contract methods. If successful, the method name, signature, and input values will be included in the log entry.

Returns: List of blocks, in ascending order by block number, each containing a list of the events in the block.
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
toBlock number <optional>

Limit results to events before the specified block (inclusive) - If not specified, will start from latest block
fromBlock number <optional>

Limit results to events after the specified block (inclusive)
count number <optional>
 10

Max number of events to include (unless both toBlock and fromBlock are unspecified)
includeTransaction boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, more detailed transaction info will be included. Note: This requires one extra network call per block, so it should not be used for very large ranges
Examples
async Events({
  "count": 5
});

ExtractEventFromLogs({
contractAddress,
abi,
event,
eventName
}) → Promise.<*>

Extract the specified event log from the given event obtained from the CallContractAndMethodAndWait method

Returns: The parsed event log from the event
See:
  • Utils.WeiToEther
Parameters:
Name Type Description
contractAddress string

Address of the contract to call the specified method on
abi Object

ABI of contract
event Object

Event of the transaction from CallContractMethodAndWait
eventName string

Name of the event to parse

ExtractValueFromEvent({
contractAddress,
abi,
event,
eventName,
eventValue
})

Extract the specified value from the specified event log from the given event obtained from the CallContractAndMethodAndWait method

Returns:

The value extracted from the event
Parameters:
Name Type Description
contractAddress string

Address of the contract to call the specified method on
abi Object

ABI of contract
event Object

Event of the transaction from CallContractMethodAndWait
eventName string

Name of the event to parse
eventValue string

Name of the value to extract from the event
Examples

async FabricUrl({
libraryIdoptional,
objectIdoptional,
versionHashoptional,
partHashoptional,
repoptional,
calloptional,
queryParamsoptional,
noAuthoptional,
noCacheoptional
}) → Promise.<string>

Generate a URL to the specified item in the content fabric with appropriate authorization token.

Returns: URL to the specified endpoint with authorization token
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
libraryId string <optional>

ID of an library
objectId string <optional>

ID of an object
versionHash string <optional>

Hash of an object version
partHash string <optional>

Hash of a part - Requires object ID
rep string <optional>

Rep parameter of the url
call string <optional>

Bitcode method to call
queryParams Object <optional>

Query params to add to the URL
noAuth boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, authorization will not be performed and the URL will not have an authorization token. This is useful for accessing public assets.
noCache boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, a new access request will be made for the authorization regardless of whether such a request exists in the client cache. This request will not be cached. This option has no effect if noAuth is true.
Examples
async FabricUrl({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks"
});

async FileUrl({
libraryId,
objectId,
versionHashoptional,
filePath,
queryParamsoptional,
noCacheoptional
}) → Promise.<string>

Generate a URL to the specified content object file with appropriate authorization token.

Returns: URL to the specified file with authorization token
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
libraryId string

ID of an library
objectId string

ID of an object - Required if using versionHash
versionHash string <optional>

Hash of an object version - If specified, will be used instead of objectID in URL
filePath string

Path to the content object file
queryParams Object <optional>

Query params to add to the URL
noCache boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, a new access request will be made for the authorization regardless of whether such a request exists in the client cache. This request will not be cached.
Examples

async Rep({
libraryId,
objectId,
versionHashoptional,
rep,
queryParamsoptional,
noAuthoptional,
noCacheoptional
}) → Promise.<string>

Generate a URL to the specified /rep endpoint of a content object. URL includes authorization token.

Alias for the FabricUrl method with the "rep" parameter

Returns: URL to the specified rep endpoint with authorization token
See:
  • FabricUrl for creating arbitrary fabric URLs
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
libraryId string

ID of the library
objectId string

ID of the object
versionHash string <optional>

Hash of the object version - if not specified, latest version will be used
rep string

Representation to use
queryParams Object <optional>

Query params to add to the URL
noAuth boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, authorization will not be performed and the URL will not have an authorization token. This is useful for accessing public assets.
noCache boolean <optional>
 false

If specified, a new access request will be made for the authorization regardless of whether such a request exists in the client cache. This request will not be cached. This option has no effect if noAuth is true.
Examples
async Rep({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",
  "objectId": "iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC",
  "rep": "image"
});


"http://localhost:8008/qlibs/ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks/q/iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC/rep/image?authorization=eyJxc3BhY2VfaWQiOiJpc3BjNDU4dTd2eGtTMm85WHlFM0hvcUVLWnVaOWg4dyIsInFsaWJfaWQiOiJpbGliVEYxM2dUOVM5ZEQ1Z012R3ZHaXlFNjZ3dGtzIiwiYWRkciI6IjB4MjFFNzM2OTVkNTFEODI5RTJiYmI1ZDQyMGY0ODc3NjEzMkFFMkU0NCIsInR4aWQiOiIweDIzOTU0MzUxMWYxZjMyYjdjY2IyNzk3MzAzZTczMWRiMzA1ZWRiNWVlNzI0Yzk3NThiZWM3NTAxYzU2NDg1MWIifQ%3D%3D.U0lHTkFUVVJF"

async ReplacePublicLibraryMetadata({
libraryId,
metadata,
metadataSubtreeoptional
})

Replace the specified library's public metadata

See:
  • PUT /qlibs/:qlibid/meta
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
libraryId string

ID of the library
metadata Object

New metadata
metadataSubtree string <optional>

Subtree to replace - modifies root metadata if not specified
Example

  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",
  "metadataSubtree": "public/toReplace",

  }
});

async SetCustomContentContract({
libraryId,
objectId,
customContractAddress,
nameoptional,
descriptionoptional,
abi,
factoryAbioptional,
overridesoptional
}) → Promise.<Object>

Set the custom contract of the specified object with the contract at the specified address

Note: This also updates the content object metadata with information about the contract - particularly the ABI

Returns: Result transaction of calling the setCustomContract method on the content object contract
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
libraryId string

ID of the library
objectId string

ID of the object
customContractAddress string

Address of the deployed custom contract
name string <optional>

Optional name of the custom contract
description string <optional>

Optional description of the custom contract
abi Object

ABI of the custom contract
factoryAbi Object <optional>

If the custom contract is a factory, the ABI of the contract it deploys
overrides Object <optional>

Change default gasPrice or gasLimit used for this action

async UploadFiles({
libraryId,
objectId,
writeToken,
fileInfo
})

Upload files to a content object. This method encapsulates the complexity of creating upload jobs and uploading data to them. It is highly recommended to use this method over using CreateFileUploadJob, UploadFileData and FinalizeUploadJobs individually

See:
  • GET /qlibs/:qlibid/q/:qhit/meta/files
Parameters:
Name Type Description
libraryId string

ID of the library
objectId string

ID of the object
writeToken string

Write token of the draft
fileInfo Array.<object>

List of files to upload, including their size, type, and contents
Example
async UploadFiles({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",
  "objectId": "iq__GPrvedQjwNDTdGqRyrko2z2ksuC",
  "writeToken": "tqw_2SHD8QcBBPp5aHzKVrXti91MzZf1FAt6p",
  "fileInfo": [
    {
      "path": "testDirectory",
      "type": "directory"
    },
    {
      "path": "testDirectory/File 1",
      "type": "file",
      "size": 100000,
      "data": "<ArrayBuffer 100000>"
    },
    {
      "path": "testDirectory/File 2",
      "type": "file",
      "size": 100000,
      "data": "<ArrayBuffer 100000>"
    }
  ]
});

async UploadPart({
libraryId,
objectId,
writeToken,
data,
chunkSizeoptional,
callbackoptional
}) → Promise.<Object>

Upload part to an object draft

Returns: Response containing information about the uploaded part
See:
  • POST /qlibs/:qlibid/q/:write_token/data
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
libraryId string

ID of the library
objectId string

ID of the object
writeToken string

Write token of the content object draft
data ArrayBuffer | Blob | Buffer

Data to upload
chunkSize number <optional>
 1000000

(1MB) - Chunk size, in bytes
callback function <optional>

If specified, function will be called with upload progress after completion of each chunk

  • Method signatue: ({uploaded, total})
Examples
async UploadPart({
  "libraryId": "ilibTF13gT9S9dD5gMvGvGiyE66wtks",

});
